 a Swiss Army Knife (™" (br) "Victorinox AG), Racket is like having a Swiss Army Knife factory." (br) "Experiencing it is well worth your time and effort, even (especially) if" (br) "you plan to use other languages mostly.") (p "The emphasis will be on *physical computing*—using the Pi to sense and" (br) "control the external world, which is the funnest fun available.") (p "Together, the Pi, Racket and some simple hardware which you can build" (br) "are a great combination of indoor adventure kit we can use on this" (br) "little escapade. I’ve stolen Hokusai-sensei’s title and hopefully" (br) "spirit–hence *32 views of computing—with Racket and Raspberry Pi*. I" (br) "like the multiple ‘views’ approach, because it provides myself and the" (br) "reader with small, hopefully approachable chunks to digest. And *32*" (br) "because, computers like powers of two.") (p "I like the multiple ‘views’ approach, because it provides us all with" (br) "small, hopefully approachable chunks to digest. And *32* because," (br) "computers like [powers of" (br) "two](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Power_of_two).") (p "The plan is to publish in segments, each available for the price of a" (br) "bowl of noodles, though sadly I won’t be offering a ring binder as a" (br) "special offer with the first one. Or noodles.") (p "### More to read") (p "[Hokusai: beyond the Great Wave–The British Museum" (br) "Blog](https://blog.britishmuseum.org/new-exhibition-announced-hokusai-beyond-the-great-wave/)") (p "[Raspberry Pi - Teach, Learn, and Make with Raspberry" (br) "Pi](https://www.raspberrypi.org)") (p "You can [sign up](https://tinyletter.com/32views) to be notified when" (br) "the first instalment is available.")))) (metas . #hasheq((here-path . "/Users/stevel/Personal/32-views/pollen/index.html.pm"))))